description: information about plants that are food

command.prompt:
Generate 2 rows for a table of information about plants that are food. The semi-colon-separated header of attributes for the table is:
Plant;Variety;Color;Fruit;Soil;Water;Temperature;Light;Pruning;Fertilizer;Pest;Taste;Days to Maturity;Nutrition Facts (per 100g)

Do not generate fictional rows. Generate the rows from real known data. Here is a list of semi-colon-separated rows not to generate by semantic key only:
Plant;Variety
Apple;Granny Smith
Asparagus;Jersey Knight
Basil, Sweet;Summer
Broccoli;Spring
Cabbage;Fall
Cherry;Rainier
Cucumber;Lemon
Eggplant;Neon
Grape;Concord
Lettuce;Romaine
Peach;August Pride
Pear;Bartlett
Radish;Cherry Belle
Raspberry;Bountiful
Spinach;Space
Squash;Acorn
Strawberry;Temptation
Tomato;Beefsteak
Watermelon;Crimson Sweet
Carrot, Daucus carota;Danvers 126
Celery, Apium graveolens;Ventura
Corn, Zea mays;Sweet Corn Incredible

Output the rows in the format of a semi-colon-separated .csv file with a column header. Then explain the source of the new data.
command.output_table:
Plant;Variety;Color;Fruit;Soil;Water;Temperature;Light;Pruning;Fertilizer;Pest;Taste;Days to Maturity;Nutrition Facts (per 100g)
Basil, Sweet;Genovese;Green;Herb;Well-drained;Moist;15-23°C;Full Sun;Pinch back;Balanced;Fusarium wilt, Gray mold;Slightly sweet, pungent;30-50 days;43 kcal, 2.04 g protein, 3.1 g fat, 3.1 g carbs, 1.7 g fiber, 105 mg vit K, 5.6 mg iron, 67 mg calcium, 36 mg magnesium
Celery, Apium graveolens;Pascal;Green;Vegetable;Moist, rich;Plentiful;7-24°C;Partial shade;Blanch;Balanced;Bacterial leaf spot, Black heart;Mildly salty, crisp;100-140 days;18 kcal, 1.1 g protein, 0.2 g fat, 3.5 g carbs, 1.6 g fiber, 134 mcg vit K, 260 mg sodium, 40 mg calcium, 32 mg magnesium
